{"pageProps":{"course":{"name":"The Novel","department":"English","description":"This course develops students' analytic and critical thought about narrative choices as well as guides students along the steps of writing an extended fictional work. It bolsters understanding of the use of setting, plot, style, theme, and characters to communicate their creative vision. Students use a writer's lens to read a variety of professional models of fiction as well as non-fiction pieces about writing. Students participate in skill building writing exercises that include annotation, analytical writing, discussion, journaling, and feedback. Upon the completion of this semester, students have completed one multi-paragraph literary analysis, a draft of an extended work of fiction, and revision of the first 10 pages of their extended works.","AtoG":"B-English","length":"Semester","prerequisites":[],"classes":[{"name":"The Novel","block":"3","semester":"Fall2014","teacher":{"name":"Lorna Galang"}},{"name":"The Novel","block":"4","semester":"Fall2014","teacher":{"name":"Anne Freeland"}},{"name":"The Novel","block":"7","semester":"Fall2014","teacher":{"name":"Lorna Galang"}},{"name":"The Novel","block":"5","semester":"Spring2015","teacher":{"name":"Anne Freeland"}},{"name":"The Novel","block":"7","semester":"Spring2015","teacher":{"name":"Anne Freeland"}},{"name":"The Novel","block":"4","semester":"Fall2015","teacher":{"name":"Lorna Galang"}},{"name":"The Novel","block":"6","semester":"Fall2015","teacher":{"name":"Lorna Galang"}},{"name":"The Novel","block":"8","semester":"Fall2015","teacher":{"name":"Lorna Galang"}},{"name":"The Novel","block":"2","semester":"Spring2016","teacher":{"name":"Anne Freeland"}},{"name":"The Novel","block":"2","semester":"Fall2016","teacher":{"name":"Kristen Mitchell"}},{"name":"The Novel","block":"4","semester":"Fall2016","teacher":{"name":"Kristen Mitchell"}},{"name":"The Novel","block":"8","semester":"Fall2016","teacher":{"name":"Anne Freeland"}},{"name